title: Times have changed
summary: If Barty Crouch Jr. were asked to find a word to describe Tish, he would be out of his mind. You'd be hard-pressed to find someone so ignorant among Muggles that she despised magic, potions, even wizards? A Muggle. How dare she despise a wizard? He knew from the first moment he met this stupid woman that he had to pay a price. Crucio or Avada Kedavel, that's up for debate. Still, he was shocked to see that the Muggle woman had survived all the magical attacks. You -- if you grew up in the wizarding world, you'd be shocked by this. She dodged an Arvada, used a shotgun before a crucio could be fired? Blew each other's brains out. Brains splattered, she dragged the wizard's body into the pigpen. She did this as naturally as if she had butchered an animal, and the sorcerer had not even had time to cry out for help before he was struck by the metal. "I said, don't be afraid of those middle-aged men with small sticks, men are like that until they die, pretending to be dead."
